Eskom spokesperson Dikatso Mothae joins us on the line. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Eskom confirmed stage 2 load-shedding will continue into Friday morning. The power utility says their systems remain constrained and unpredictable. READ: Eskom: Stage 2 load-shedding 'highly likely' "Our emergency reserves are insufficient to meet the demands for electricity during the day," Eskom said in a statement. The utility asked customers to reduce demand. Watch the full interview with Eskom spokesperson Dikatso Mothae in the video above.